te web |url=https://open.spotify.com/album/5XpjnV9EuzkH60PtpwHn1E?si=bcMZea4jTFiKpm6j93YeRg|title=Location|publisher=[[Spotify]]|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/location-single/id1147282471|title=Location - Single By Khalid|work=iTunes|accessdate=January 12, 2017}}</ref> The track was produced by Syk Sense, Tunji Ige, and Chris McClenney, with additional production from Smash David, Alfredo Gonzalez, and Taz Taylor.<ref name=\"RWD\">{{cite web|url=http://rwdmag.com/khalids-location-is-a-tale-of-young-love-beyond-its-years/|title=Khalid's \"Location\" Is A Tale Of Love Beyond Its Years|publisher=RWDMag|accessdate=January 12, 2017}}</ref><ref>https://soundcloud.com/thegreatkhalid/location-prod-by-syk-sense-tunji-ige-smash-david</ref><ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BRMD650DMCc/</ref> The song was certified 7x [[RIAA certification|Platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]] (RIAA) and was recorded at Beacon Hill Recording Studios.<ref>http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/khalids-location-goes-platinum-news.32719.html</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/hughmcintyre/2019/08/15/khalids-debut-album-matches-a-feat-only-accomplished-by-cardi-b-and-twenty-one-pilots/|title=Khalid's Debut Album Matches A Feat Accomplished By Only Cardi B And Twenty One Pilots|last=McIntyre|first=Hugh|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref> The official remix featuring [[Lil Wayne]] and [[Kehlani]] was released on March 17, 2017, another remix featuring [[Little Simz]] was released on January 26, 2017, and a third official remix featuring [[Jorja Smith]] and [[Wretch 32]] was released on February 9, 2018. \u201cLocation\u201d was nominated for [[Best R&B Song]] at the [[60th Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/artists/khalid|title=Khalid|date=2019-11-26|website=GRAMMY.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\nWhile talking about the song in an interview with ''[[Pigeons & Planes]]'', Khalid expressed his passion of the song's beat:\n\n<blockquote>\"Location\" is a song that came to me out of nowhere. From the first time I heard the beat play, the words flew out. Hearing the chords instantly took me the first stage of a relationship. Young love, man. It\u2019s a crazy thing. I first started making music in the winter of 2015 so this is one of my most developed songs so far.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pigeonsandplanes.com/music/2016/05/khalid-location|title=The New Wave: Khalid - \"Location\"|work=[[Pigeons & Planes]]|date=May 10, 2016|accessdate=January 12, 2017}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n==Music video==\nThe song's accompanying music video premiered on September 26, 2016, on Khalid's [[Vevo]] account on [[YouTube]] and was directed by Alex Di Marco. As of February 3, 2020, the music video has over 442 million views.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=by3yRdlQvzs|title=Khalid - Location|first=|last=KhalidVEVO|date=21 August 2017|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n*;Digital download\n#\u201dLocation\u201d (Remix) (featuring [[Lil Wayne]] and [[Kehlani]]) \u2013 4:38\n\n*;Digital download\n#\u201dLocation\u201d (London Remix) (featuring [[Little Simz]]) \u2013 4:05\n\n*;Digital download\n#\u201dLocation\u201d (Remix) (featuring [[Jorja Smith]] and [[Wretch 32]]) \u2013 3:29\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017\u201318)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=August 14, 2017|accessdate=August 12, 2017}}</ref>\n| 39\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders Tip|16|artist=Khalid|song=Location|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 22, 2017