on the Beats]]\n* Mae N. Maejor\n* Remo the Hitmaker\n* Smash David\n* Young Stokes\n}}\n| prev_title = [[Welcome to JFK]]\n| prev_year  = 2015\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Legends Never Die\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = For the Love\n | single1date = April 11, 2016\n | single2     = Like This\n | single2date = May 17, 2016\n}}\n}}\n'''''Legends Never Die''''' is the second and final [[studio album]] by American [[Hip hop music|hip hop]] recording artist [[Chinx]]. The album was released on September 16, 2016, by [[Entertainment One Music]], [[Coke Boys Records]], Riot Squad and NuSense Music Group.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/stream-chinxs-posthumous-album-legends-never-die-news.24132.html|title=Stream Chinx's Posthumous Album \"Legends Never Die\"|accessdate=September 17, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Singles==\nOn April 11, 2016, the album's lead [[Single (music)|single]] \"For the Love\" featuring Meet Sims was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/for-love-feat.-meet-sims-single/id1103382003/|title=For the Love (feat. Meet Sims) - Single by Chinx on Apple Music|publisher=}}</ref> On May 17, 2016, the album's second single \"Like This\" featuring [[Chrisette Michele]] and Meet Sims was released.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hotnewhiphop.com/chinx-like-this-feat-chrisette-michele-and-meetsims-new-song.1969829.html|title=Chinx  - Like This Feat. Chrisette Michele & MeetSims - Stream [New Song]|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| total_length = \n\n| title1 = Like This\n| note1 = featuring [[Chrisette Michele]] and Meet Sims\n| extra1 = Young Stokes\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Chinx|Lionel Pickens]]|[[Chrisette Michele|Chrisette Payne]]|Derwin Armstrong|Doug Ellison||Turrell Sims}}\n| length1 = 3:13\n\n| title2 = Match That\n| extra2 = {{hlist|Smash David|Austin Powerz|[[Lee on the Beats]]}}\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Pickens|Austin S